Installation
============

Executing **install-gnu.sh** from a unix shell will start the build process.
The default installation directory is the folder *dep* located in the root
directory of this project.

```./install-gnu.sh```

Changing the installation directory
-----------------------------------

You can change the installation directory by specifying a path as an argument:
```./install-gnu.sh custom-path```

=Linux=

The following packages are required in order to compile the dependencies
successfully:
```
freeglut3-dev libglew-dev libxrandr-dev
```


